      • isBlockPlace

        public static boolean isBlockPlace(byte packetID)
        Is this the packet where the client places a block? On 1.7.10 - 1.8.8 the client sends a PacketPlayInBlockPlace packet when actually placing the block. On 1.9 - now the client sends a PacketPlayInUseItem packet when placing the block and the PacketPlayInBlockPlace has a different use. This method is a nice utility supporting all these versions letting you know if the client played a block. The WrappedPacketInBlockPlace wrapper only works on an actual block place. Use this method before using the wrapper to support all minecraft versions.
        Parameters:
        packetID - Play Packet ID.
        Returns:
        Has the client placed a block?
